<%  if params[:load_all] 
      @new_tasks ||= @tasks
    else
      @new_tasks ||= @tasks - @this_user.tasks.active.unorganized.recent.three
    end %>
<div id="tasks_page" class="pager" data-children_pages="({<%= "'#{multiple_tasks_url(:ids => @new_tasks.map{|t| t.id}.join(','))}':'multiple_tasks_page_#{@new_tasks.map{|t| t.id}.join('_')}','#{dashboard_url}':'dashboard_overview'" %>})">
<%= render :partial => '/layouts/subnav' %>
<div class="page_layout">
<% if @tasks.length > 0 %>
  <h2>Unorganized Tasks</h2>
  <div id="unarchived_items_wrapper" class="list_container">
  	<% @tasks.each_with_index do |task,index| %>
  		<div id="task_<%= task.id %>" class="row border_bottom" data-list_index="<%= index %>">
  		<%= render :partial => '/tasks/show', :locals => {:task => task, :needs_organization => true, :pager_target => "multiple_tasks_page_#{@new_tasks.map{|t| t.id}.join('_')}"} %>
  		</div>
  	<% end %>
  </div>
  <%= will_paginate @tasks %>
  <div id="archive_completed_items" class="list_action button round color2" <% unless @this_user.tasks.complete.unorganized.any? %>style="display: none;"<% end %>>
    	<span onclick="void(0)" href="<%= archive_completed_tasks_url %>"
    	 	data-ajax_behavior="ajax_link"
    		data-ajax_method="GET"
    		data-ajax_success_callback="handleArchivementSuccess();" >archive completed tasks</span>
  </div>
<% else %>
  <h2>You don't have any unorganized tasks right now.</h2>
  <% if @this_user.show_help_text %>
  
  <div class="explanatory">
    <p>When you use the dashboard to add a task, it's a quick way to get it into the system. Later when you have more time, preferably daily, you should come back and review the tasks you've added. You'll find them here, in the Unorganized Task list.<br/>&nbsp;<br/>While you're reviewing your new tasks you can check off any you've already completed and consider yourself accomplished. If you haven't completed a task, consider adding it to a plan or a label. If it is a task that involves multiple steps itself, you can convert it to a plan and add tasks to that plan to list the steps.</p>
  </div>
  <% end %>
<% end %>
</div>
</div>
